    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the Native American people who inhabited the upper James River valley of Virginia,  or the present-day group in Amherst County, Virginia, claiming descent from these people. Distinct from the "Algonkin" who share the same original Algonquian language heritage, but inhabit Northern Ontario and Quebec along the Ottawa River in Canada.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
